Package test.gov.cdc.izgateway

Class NamedArrayList

java.lang.Object
java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
java.util.AbstractList<E>
java.util.ArrayList<String>
test.gov.cdc.izgateway.NamedArrayList
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Comparable<NamedArrayList>, Iterable<String>, Collection<String>, List<String>, RandomAccess
public class NamedArrayList extends ArrayList<String> implements Comparable<NamedArrayList>
NamedArrayList is used to make automated lists test cases which are intended to be extensive in what they test. They enable test inputs to be automatically generated once and cached for reuse when needed again later without repeating the expensive generation process. There may be to many cases for for routine testing, so it also offers the capability to generate a selection from the total set for more frequent regression testing vs. release testing.
